### Understand Vercel AI SDK streaming events
The Vercel AI SDK's `streamText` function provides a `fullStream` property that returns all stream events.
Each event includes a `type` property which describes the event type.
A complete text response can be constructed from the following event types:
- `text-start`: Signals the start of a text response.
Contains an `id` to correlate subsequent events.
- `text-delta`: Contains a single text token in the `text` field.
These events represent incremental text chunks as the model generates them.
- `text-end`: Signals the completion of a text response.

